description.narrative: UNICEF engaged in strategic partnerships with the national television and a national newspaper on children's rights reporting, and the participation of the Network of Children and Young Journalists children in the production and broadcast of contents. In addition, UNICEF supported a total of 22 public advocacy activities to advocate for children's rights. Most of these activities were led by and for children and young people, through active engagement of the Children's Parliament and network and young reporters. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
